Are you serious?

00:09:32.420 --> 00:09:33.260
Yes.

00:09:33.780 --> 00:09:37.740
I think we should tell the police
about the game.

00:09:39.060 --> 00:09:43.340
l think it's important information
for catching the murderer this time.

00:09:43.410 --> 00:09:45.450
You relate it with the game again?

00:09:46.920 --> 00:09:47.760
Actually,

00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:51.240
there was a birthday cake
at Mrs Akaike's flat,

00:09:51.920 --> 00:09:55.160
and "Misato Akaike" was written
on the chocolate plaque.

00:09:55.440 --> 00:09:59.160
Usually it should say
"Happy birthday, someone," right?

00:10:00.080 --> 00:10:03.340
But it was only the name,
Misato Akaike.

00:10:07.940 --> 00:10:10.100
What? You say that Mrs Akaike

00:10:10.180 --> 00:10:12.060
was killed in the game
based on that?

00:10:12.140 --> 00:10:12.980
That's all?

00:10:13.100 --> 00:10:14.860
Not based on that, but...

00:10:14.940 --> 00:10:20.100
lt's the same as saying that someone
among us killed Mr and Mrs Akaike.

00:10:20.220 --> 00:10:21.580
That's not what l mean.

00:10:24.900 --> 00:10:26.460
What do you mean, then?

00:10:28.060 --> 00:10:28.980
Actually...

00:10:29.900 --> 00:10:33.540
l also think that it's better
if we tell the police,

00:10:34.260 --> 00:10:35.220
but...

00:10:35.740 --> 00:10:40.300
what about the inducement of murder
we talked about the other day?

00:10:40.620 --> 00:10:44.540
I don't know very well either.

00:10:45.140 --> 00:10:46.540
I didn't do anything,

00:10:46.820 --> 00:10:49.360
so l don't want to be seen
as the murderer's accomplice.

00:10:49.800 --> 00:10:50.920
Mrs lshizaki,

00:10:51.280 --> 00:10:54.480
didn't you say you wrote your name
on the piece of paper?

00:10:55.120 --> 00:10:59.220
Make sure you don't kill me
by mistake.

00:10:59.620 --> 00:11:01.260
Yes, so?

00:11:01.740 --> 00:11:04.340
Instead of worrying
about being killed,

00:11:04.420 --> 00:11:06.660
you worry more about being seen
as an accomplice?

00:11:07.580 --> 00:11:08.700
What's your point?

00:11:10.380 --> 00:11:13.020
I just thought you were the murderer
for a bit.

00:11:13.340 --> 00:11:15.900
What? You...

00:11:16.540 --> 00:11:17.910
Sorry, l am late.

00:11:25.110 --> 00:11:26.660
Are you all right?

00:11:28.860 --> 00:11:30.440
Why do you ask?

00:11:31.400 --> 00:11:34.020
Mrs Tamiya
said you weren't feeling well.

00:11:35.060 --> 00:11:37.280
I am all right. What's the topic?

00:11:38.680 --> 00:11:44.800
Mrs Tezuka suggests that we should
tell the police about the game.

00:11:47.720 --> 00:11:49.400
I'll let you make the decision.

00:11:50.160 --> 00:11:52.500
We can't reach a conclusion
on our own,

00:11:52.780 --> 00:11:54.980
so we would like your opinion.

00:11:57.780 --> 00:11:58.620
Yes?

00:12:00.500 --> 00:12:02.220
I have looked it up,

00:12:02.700 --> 00:12:05.220
and l don't think we'll be arrested.

00:12:05.620 --> 00:12:06.460
Really?

00:12:06.540 --> 00:12:11.310
But all of us could be treated
as murderers for a while.

00:12:12.590 --> 00:12:14.710
- That would be awful.
- But...

00:12:14.830 --> 00:12:17.350
We'll be in trouble
if gossip magazines sniff anything.

00:12:17.910 --> 00:12:21.790
They'll say this is a condo full
of murder suspects and cause a stir.

00:12:21.910 --> 00:12:23.990
I think you're exaggerating it.

00:12:30.190 --> 00:12:32.150
Murderers' condo</i>

00:12:32.270 --> 00:12:35.110
lf they add an exclamation mark
and a question mark,

00:12:35.190 --> 00:12:37.030
they can write
almost anything they want.

00:12:37.110 --> 00:12:38.550
It's over if they do this.

00:12:38.670 --> 00:12:40.510
Even if we're found innocent
at the end,

00:12:40.590 --> 00:12:42.430
it'll stay on the internet forever.

00:12:43.350 --> 00:12:44.590
Mrs lshizaki,

00:12:44.830 --> 00:12:47.730
your children's classmates will call
your kids "murderer's children."

00:12:48.410 --> 00:12:50.650
Our properties' value
will drop rapidly too.

00:12:50.850 --> 00:12:54.030
It's like our whole residential
tower is a stigmatised property.

00:12:54.220 --> 00:12:56.780
Fujii got most desperate
and he's suspicious.

00:12:56.860 --> 00:12:57.820
Don't make fun of me!

00:12:57.940 --> 00:12:58.860
Fine.

00:12:59.300 --> 00:13:02.420
How can you be so calm?

00:13:03.020 --> 00:13:04.380
We are all terrified!

00:13:06.060 --> 00:13:07.900
Are you calm
because you're the murderer?

00:13:08.700 --> 00:13:10.140
What do you mean?

00:13:10.300 --> 00:13:11.300
This isn't right.

00:13:11.380 --> 00:13:13.220
- Miss Ono.
- Please calm down.

00:13:13.300 --> 00:13:14.960
- Mrs lshizaki too.
- What do you mean?

00:13:15.040 --> 00:13:17.520
- You said l was the murderer!
- l didn't.

00:13:17.600 --> 00:13:19.120
You did!

00:13:19.800 --> 00:13:22.040
Among these three people?

00:13:22.280 --> 00:13:24.160
Did they come to buy
a birthday cake?

00:13:24.360 --> 00:13:26.360
I don't remember their faces.

00:13:26.520 --> 00:13:28.520
Did you keep the receipt?

00:13:28.640 --> 00:13:30.320
We did, just a moment, please.

00:13:40.920 --> 00:13:42.000
Well...

00:13:42.520 --> 00:13:46.800
You are scared because Mrs Tezuka
wants to report us to the police.

00:13:47.320 --> 00:13:48.280
"Report"?

00:13:48.440 --> 00:13:51.840
You guys are fishy because
you are afraid of the police.

00:13:55.160 --> 00:13:57.520
Let's calm down.

00:13:57.760 --> 00:14:02.040
You see, someone knocked his hand on
the desk and injured himself before.

00:14:02.280 --> 00:14:03.560
Yes, l did.

00:14:03.880 --> 00:14:06.080
Sorry for causing you trouble.

00:14:06.200 --> 00:14:07.400
It's totally healed now.

00:14:07.520 --> 00:14:09.960
I'm not young anymore,
I'm ashamed of what l did...

00:14:10.040 --> 00:14:11.480
l am sorry.

00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:12.400
Yes?

00:14:12.480 --> 00:14:13.360
I was joking.

00:14:14.240 --> 00:14:15.240
What joke?

00:14:15.320 --> 00:14:17.240
You don't get it, old man.

00:14:17.720 --> 00:14:20.200
Mr Tamiya's seriousness isn't funny
at all,

00:14:20.280 --> 00:14:22.640
but it makes me happy to see it
after a long while.

00:14:27.360 --> 00:14:28.400
In the end,

00:14:28.880 --> 00:14:31.000
what are we going to do?

00:14:31.480 --> 00:14:34.520
I have been living here for years,

00:14:34.920 --> 00:14:37.960
so l know that none of us
is a murderer.

00:14:38.200 --> 00:14:41.200
But Mrs Tezuka just moved here,

00:14:41.360 --> 00:14:44.520
so l think she just
doesn't understand that.

00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:46.680
Please don't blame her.

00:14:47.320 --> 00:14:49.720
The murderer wasn't caught
on camera, Mr Tamiya?

00:14:50.240 --> 00:14:51.800
You put many in the building.

00:14:54.480 --> 00:14:57.960
I haven't been recording lately.

00:14:58.720 --> 00:15:01.000
What were you trying to do, then?

00:15:02.200 --> 00:15:03.440
I feel ashamed of myself.

00:15:05.040 --> 00:15:07.320
Everyone, l am sorry.

00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:11.560
First of all,
were Mr and Mrs Akaike murdered?

00:15:12.840 --> 00:15:15.760
They could be having a fight
and it turned ugly.

00:15:16.160 --> 00:15:17.200
Relating it to the game

00:15:17.280 --> 00:15:19.260
based on the chocolate plaque
is unreasonable.

00:15:19.340 --> 00:15:21.320
I think the couple
didn't have a fight.

00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:22.400
Right?

00:15:24.760 --> 00:15:26.690
Let the police investigate this.

00:15:27.370 --> 00:15:28.960
If it's just a hunch,

00:15:29.120 --> 00:15:32.250
it's pointless if our mere guesses
make things awkward between us.

00:15:32.330 --> 00:15:34.170
Then we have to tell them
about the game.

00:15:34.250 --> 00:15:37.410
Then we need everyone's consent.

00:15:38.050 --> 00:15:41.330
Someone joined the game,
but is absent today.

00:15:43.370 --> 00:15:45.090
You mean Ms Kitagawa?

00:15:48.890 --> 00:15:50.050
I'm home.

00:15:52.330 --> 00:15:53.200
Sora?

00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:55.330
Sora, l am home.

00:15:59.490 --> 00:16:02.410
If there's a possibility
that all of us will be suspected,

00:16:02.850 --> 00:16:05.330
we have to get
Mrs Kitagawa consent too.

00:16:07.730 --> 00:16:09.890
Let's make the decision later, then.

00:16:10.650 --> 00:16:12.490
We'll decide later.

00:16:14.930 --> 00:16:16.210
Are you not scared?

00:16:18.890 --> 00:16:22.860
I carelessly wrote the name
of someone l know.

00:16:24.540 --> 00:16:27.940
Frankly, it's a long story
and l hate the person.

00:16:29.060 --> 00:16:33.660
But when l think that they might be
killed, I'm absolutely terrified.

00:16:46.460 --> 00:16:47.780
Oh, hello.

00:16:48.580 --> 00:16:49.480
Hello.

00:16:51.080 --> 00:16:53.540
It was horrible, wasn't it?

00:16:56.380 --> 00:16:59.700
Oh, l watched that.
lt was interesting.

00:17:00.180 --> 00:17:01.580
What did you watch?

00:17:01.700 --> 00:17:03.820
The musical movie you recommended.

00:17:07.140 --> 00:17:10.410
I recommended a few.
Which one was it?

00:17:12.330 --> 00:17:16.370
If a film l watch is interesting,
l forget its title.

00:17:16.970 --> 00:17:20.770
The thought that the film
is interesting occupies my mind...

00:17:23.730 --> 00:17:24.930
What the heck?

00:17:25.130 --> 00:17:29.330
Well then, let's vote.

00:17:29.890 --> 00:17:31.370
Is that okay?

00:17:32.250 --> 00:17:34.530
I think it's the only way.

00:17:35.210 --> 00:17:36.130
Okay.

00:17:36.970 --> 00:17:39.050
- Then...
- lt was just once.

00:17:39.730 --> 00:17:42.930
A murder just happened by chance.

00:17:43.370 --> 00:17:47.730
If you want to make all residents
here suspects, then raise your hand.

00:17:48.050 --> 00:17:50.530
